# Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values. **Never commit `.env` to Git.**

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

## Required variables

| Variable | Where to get it |
|---|---|
| `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` | Supabase → Project Settings → API → Project URL |
| `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Supabase → Project Settings → API → anon public key |
| `VITE_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` | Telegram → @BotFather → /newbot |

```env
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here
VITE_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your-bot-token-here
```

## Setting variables on Vercel

In the Vercel dashboard → your project → **Settings → Environment Variables**, add each key above with its value. Vercel automatically injects them at build time.
